abstract: CHICAGO, June 26. -- Provisions were active, very nervous, and very irregular to-day. The newspapers contained the report of a yellow-fever case in quarantine at New-Orleans. The statement, on the heels of the uncomfortable interview by the Government microscopist at the stock yards, put the trade in a very uncomfortable frame of mind. Before the report was denied or explained pork dropped 10c a bbl; lard and ribs, 2 1/2 5c.

abstract: CAPE MAY POINT, N.J., June 27. -- Postmaster General Wanamaker came down to-night to enjoy the sea breezes over Sunday. He appeared to enjoy the prospect of his brief rest.

abstract: At the tenth annual games of the Kings Country wheelmen at Washington Park, Brooklyn, yesterday, A.A. Zimmerman of the New-York Athletic Club won the one-mile ordinary championship of America. Murphy of the Kings County wheelmen.

abstract: LONDON, June 28. -- Money was abundant during the week, and there was no demand for discount, which was quoted at 1 1/2 3/4. The Stock Exchange continues lethargic. Apart from the steady current of investment buying of high-class stocks, nothing is doing. Dealers concur in the opinion that speculative business is at its lowest ebb. Never before has such a prolonged period of inaction been experienced.

abstract: PHILADELPHIA, June 29. -- Ten innings were required to determine the game here to-day between Philadelphia and Brooklyn, and the latter won in a most brilliant manner.
